HELP FOR BUTTONS
1. New - Creates a new map. Enter dimensions in the form XxZxY or XxZ 
	(e.g 10x20x2 - will create a grid of 10 rows and 20 columns with 2 levels)
	(e.g. 10x20 - will create a grid of 10 rows and 20 columns with 1 level)
2. Save - Opens a file dialog to choose file name. Saves a pickle of the data model
3. Load - Opens a file dialog to choose file name. Loads a previously saved data model
3. Connect - Connects to sever using details entered in the craftBuilder.py file
4. Disconnect - Disconnects from server
5. Clear Level - Removes all blocks from the current level
6. Delete Level - Deletes the current level
7. Insert Level - Inserts a level below the current level
8. Combo box (Curr. Level/Overlay Level) - Selects Current level visible and the overlay level to be shown
9. Copy overlay Level - Copies the blocks from the overlay level to the current level
10. New Level - Adds a level to the top of current levels
11. Rotate - Rotates the model 90 degrees anti-clockwise
12. Overlay toggle - toggles whether an overlay of another level is visible or not. The overlay is represented by thicker grid boxes
13. Item combo box - Selects the block kind (1-63)
14. Load from world - Loads the block representation from the world. Specify the bottom left block and the top right block of the imaginary cube that contains the area you want copied to the model
15. Paste in world - Pastes the current model on the world given a set of world x,y,z co-ordinates which acts as the origin point (0,0,0) of the model. All model points will be pasted related to that point
16. Paste Signs - Pastes the signs if the model you are using contains signs. They will be rotated when the model is rotated.
17. Add Geometry - This option is available if builder.py is in the directory. You can add geometric shapes to your model using this option

